name: Goji Berry
des: Goji Berry is a nutritious and delicious dried fruit known for its health benefits. It is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, making it a popular choice among health-conscious consumers.

name: Kidney bean
des: Kidney beans are a type of legume known for their kidney shape and rich protein content. They are commonly used in various dishes, including chili, soups, and salads.

name: Carrot
des: Carrots are root vegetables known for their bright orange color and crunchy texture. They are a good source of vitamins and are often enjoyed raw, cooked, or juiced.

name: Apple Fruit
des: Apples are one of the most popular fruits globally, known for their sweet and refreshing taste. They are a good source of fiber and essential nutrients, making them a healthy snack option.

name: split peas
des: Split peas are dried and peeled seeds of peas, commonly used in soups and stews. They are rich in protein, fiber, and various vitamins, making them a nutritious addition to meals.

name: WaterMelon
des: Watermelon is a juicy and refreshing fruit enjoyed during hot summer days. It is high in water content and contains vitamins and antioxidants, making it a hydrating and healthy option.

name: Mango Fruit
des: Mango is a tropical fruit loved for its sweet and luscious flavor. It is packed with vitamins, minerals, and dietary fiber, making it a delicious and nutritious choice for snacks and desserts.

name: mung beans
des: Mung beans, also known as green gram, are small green legumes commonly used in Asian cuisines. They are rich in protein and easy to cook, making them a staple ingredient in various dishes.

name: Jujube Date Palm
des: Jujube Date Palm, commonly known as red dates or Chinese dates, is a sweet and nutritious dried fruit. It is a popular snack and often used in traditional herbal medicine for its health benefits.

name: Apricot Fruit
des: Apricot is a small, orange-colored fruit with a sweet and tangy taste. It is rich in vitamins A and C and provides various health benefits, including improved eye health and immune support.

name: pianapple Fruit
des: Pineapple is a tropical fruit known for its sweet and tropical flavor. It is a good source of vitamin C and manganese and is commonly used in fruit salads, smoothies, and desserts.

name: Tomato
des: Tomato is a versatile and widely used vegetable that is botanically a fruit. It is a rich source of lycopene, an antioxidant known for its health benefits, and is a key ingredient in many dishes worldwide.

name: Gooseberry
des: Gooseberry, also known as amla or Indian gooseberry, is a small green fruit with a tangy and sour taste. It is a rich source of vitamin C and antioxidants and is used in various culinary and medicinal applications.

name: Dal Chickpea
des: Dal Chickpea, also known as Chana Dal, is a split and husked chickpea used in Indian cooking. It is a good source of plant-based protein and is often used in dal recipes, soups, and curries.

name: Persimmon
des: Persimmon is a sweet and flavorful fruit with a unique texture. It comes in two main varieties - Fuyu and Hachiya. Persimmons are a good source of vitamins A and C and provide a delightful addition to fruit salads and desserts.

name: Quince Fruit
des: Quince is a fragrant fruit with a yellowish-gold color. It is often used for making jams, jellies, and other preserves due to its natural pectin content. Quince has a unique taste that becomes sweeter when cooked.

name: Custard Apple
des: Custard Apple, also known as Sitaphal or Sugar Apple, is a tropical fruit with a creamy and sweet pulp. It is rich in vitamins and minerals and is often eaten fresh or used to make milkshakes and desserts.

name: Muskmelon
des: Muskmelon, also known as Cantaloupe, is a juicy and aromatic fruit with a sweet and refreshing taste. It is high in vitamins A and C and is a popular choice for fruit salads and smoothies.

name: potato
des: Potato is a starchy tuber vegetable and is a staple food in many cuisines. It is a good source of carbohydrates and provides essential nutrients. Potatoes are used in various dishes, including mashed potatoes, fries, and curries.

name: Cabbage
des: Cabbage is a leafy green vegetable with a mild and crunchy texture. It is a good source of fiber, vitamins, and minerals. Cabbage is often used in salads, stir-fries, and coleslaw.

name: pomegranate
des: Pomegranate is a vibrant red fruit with juicy arils (seeds) inside. It is rich in antioxidants and is known for its potential health benefits. Pomegranate seeds can be enjoyed on their own, in salads, or as a topping for various dishes.

name: Cauliflower
des: Cauliflower is a cruciferous vegetable that comes in white, purple, and green varieties. It is a versatile vegetable that can be roasted, steamed, or mashed. Cauliflower is low in calories and a good source of vitamins and minerals.

name: Grape Fruit
des: Grapes are small, sweet, and juicy fruits that grow in clusters. They come in various colors like green, red, and black. Grapes are not only delicious but also provide various health benefits, being rich in antioxidants and vitamins.

name: Cucumber
des: Cucumber is a refreshing and hydrating vegetable with a mild taste. It is often used in salads, sandwiches, and as a garnish for various dishes. Cucumbers are low in calories and a good source of vitamins and minerals.

name: Stoberry Fruit

name: navy beans
des: Navy beans, also known as haricot beans, are small, creamy-white beans with a mild flavor. They are commonly used in soups, stews, and casseroles. Navy beans are a good source of protein and dietary fiber.

name: peanuts
des: Peanuts are a popular legume that grows underground. They are often consumed roasted, salted, or made into peanut butter. Peanuts are a good source of healthy fats, protein, and various vitamins and minerals.

name: pinto beans
des: Pinto beans are small, speckled beans that become pink when cooked. They are commonly used in Mexican and Southwestern cuisine, especially in dishes like chili and burritos. Pinto beans are a good source of plant-based protein and fiber.

name: Kiwi Fruit
des: Kiwi fruit is a small, green fruit with a sweet and tangy flavor. It is rich in vitamin C, vitamin K, and dietary fiber. Kiwi fruit is often eaten fresh or used as a topping for yogurt and fruit salads.

name: Dal Bean

name: Jackfruit

name: mango

name: soybeans

name: assorted nuts
des: Assorted nuts refer to a mix of different nuts such as almonds, walnuts, cashews, and pistachios. They are a great source of healthy fats, protein, and essential nutrients. Assorted nuts are often enjoyed as a nutritious snack.

name: papaya
des: Papaya is a tropical fruit with orange flesh and black seeds. It has a sweet taste with a hint of acidity. Papaya is enjoyed fresh, in smoothies, or as a topping for yogurt and desserts.

name: chickpeas

name: pear

name: Cherries

name: brinjal

name: dates

name: beans

name: pistachios

name: oranges

name: sweet potatoes

name: plum

name: garlic
des: Garlic is a pungent and flavorful vegetable that is widely used in cooking. It adds a unique taste to various dishes and is known for its potential health benefits. Garlic is often used in sauces, marinades, and as a seasoning.

name: sunflower seeds
des: Sunflower seeds are small, edible seeds that come from the sunflower plant. They are often enjoyed as a snack, added to salads, or used in baking. Sunflower seeds are a good source of healthy fats and protein.

name: cabbage
des: Cabbage is a leafy green or purple vegetable with a dense and crunchy texture. It is often used in salads, coleslaw, stir-fries, and soups. Cabbage is low in calories and rich in nutrients.

name: chia seeds
des: Chia seeds are small seeds that come from the Salvia hispanica plant. They are rich in omega-3 fatty acids, fiber, and antioxidants. Chia seeds are often added to smoothies, yogurt, and used in baking.

name: broccoli
des: Broccoli is a nutritious green vegetable that is rich in vitamins, minerals, and fiber. It has a unique appearance with a tree-like shape. Broccoli can be steamed, roasted, stir-fried, or enjoyed raw as a healthy snack.

name: mixed nuts
des: Mixed nuts are a delicious combination of different nuts like almonds, cashews, walnuts, and pistachios. They are often enjoyed as a nutritious and satisfying snack. Mixed nuts can also be used in baking and cooking.

name: yellow bell pepper
des: Yellow bell pepper is a vibrant and sweet-tasting vegetable that is rich in vitamin C and antioxidants. It adds a burst of color to dishes and can be used in salads, stir-fries, and stuffed with various fillings.

name: banana
des: Banana is a popular and nutritious fruit that comes in a natural yellow packaging. It is a great source of potassium and carbohydrates, making it a favorite among athletes. Bananas can be eaten as they are or used in smoothies, desserts, and baking.
